{
  "stem": "7744.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I stayed in at least four different hostels.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I stayed in a place called Visingso, which is an island.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I stayed in Billeshom.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then, towards the end, when most of the people left Sweden and just a few of us were left behind, because I could not immigrate to Canada-- and that's another story-- and I couldn't go to Israel because I still had tuberculosis, I lived as a little bit of a helper with a family in Stockholm.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the tuberculosis did not clear up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But on a false x-ray, I came to Canada three years after the war, in 1948.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had an aunt-- I had an aunt here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "This aunt is no longer with us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I came to live with her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I was OK, but I did have some spots on my lungs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Would you believe it that I knew exactly the address and the name?",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was something that I was made to memorize.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was my father's sister, but I was made to memorize that name.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, I contacted my aunt very soon after I was liberated.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I-- the letter that went to my aunt was-- the-- the number of the house was very close, maybe two-- two-- now two digits.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can I go back a little bit?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was in Sweden, and I found my aunt, my mother's brother, who was also a survivor of the Holocaust, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] started looking for the family.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He looked for my mother.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He looked for me.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
